<SLUG> BC-BBA-SIGNING-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANGELS GIVE BIG CHECK TO SIGN BOOTCHECK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GORDON VERRELL  
 c.2000 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ The Anaheim Angels and first-round draft pick
Chris Bootcheck ended their prolonged negotiations Friday by
agreeing to terms on a contract with a bonus believed to be about
$1.75 million.
</P>
<P>
   Bootcheck, a right-handed pitcher from Auburn University, was
the Angels' second pick in the first round of last June's
free-agent amateur draft and the 20th player selected overall.
Reportedly, Bootcheck, who was advised by player agent Scott Boras,
had originally sought a signing bonus of $2.1 million. The Angels'
first offer of $1.5 million was rejected.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels' earlier first-round pick, left-hander Joe Torres,
the 10th player taken overall, received a $2.08 million signing
bonus.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot to like about Chris Bootcheck,'' Angels scouting
director Donny Rowland said. ``He has a high ceiling.''
</P>
<P>
   In a statement issued by the Angels, Bootcheck, who was 25-10 in
his three-year career at Auburn, said: ``I'm happy to be a member
of the Anaheim Angels organization. I'm looking forward to working
toward my ultimate goal of pitching in the major leagues and being
a productive member of the Angels.''
</P>
<P>
   Bootcheck will join the Angels' instructional-league team in
Arizona Sept. 17.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
