   3-graf refer:
</P>
<P>
   ACTIVIST-PRIESTS (New York) _ In the era of Vatican II, many
Roman Catholic priests were interpreting the gospels as a call to
social action. They fought for integration and school
decentralization, built housing for the poor, and spoke out on
everything from nuclear disarmament to the Vietnam War. But today,
as the priests who first embraced Vatican II prepare for
retirement, they move with self-doubt and a measure of
disillusionment. While the evidence of their labors is everywhere
evident, their social values have by and large been abandoned by
many newer, more conservative priests. By Diana Jean Schemo.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 2 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   2-graf refer:
</P>
<P>
   NICARAGUA-LAND (Nagarote, Nicaragua) _ More than a decade after
the elections that removed the Sandinistas from power, thousands of
Nicaraguans _ as well as about 900 American citizens _ are
grappling with the legacy of the Sandinista Revolution: confiscated
land, homes and businesses that were distributed to peasants and
party loyalists. While few people expected to get back all they
owned, even skeptics decried what they described as convoluted,
lengthy administrative and legal processes that too often result in
paltry settlements paid in low-value government bonds. By David
Gonzalez.
</P>
