<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 17:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7622 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-OLY-NEW-SPORTS0910-CO     09-09 0536
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OLY-NEW-SPORTS0910-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Triathlon, synchro diving among the new arrivals
 &HT;    By Karen Rosen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Since the Olympics began 104 years ago with 43 events,
the Games continue to change with the times.
</P>
<P>
   Sydney will offer 300 events, including two new sports _
taekwondo and triathlon _ and various additions and wrinkles to
existing sports.
</P>
<P>
   Some new events waltzed into the Olympics, while others had to
muscle their way onto the schedule through intensive lobbying.
Contrary to some reports, ballroom dancing is not one of them.
</P>
<P>
   And once a sport is on the schedule, it doesn't mean it's good
to go forever. Whitewater slalom canoe/kayak had to fight tooth and
paddle to keep its place on the program.
</P>
<P>
   One result of the evolving Olympics is that more women will
participate in Sydney than in any other Games. Of the 10,000-plus
competitors, 38 percent will be female, an increase from 34 percent
in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   The following changes will take place in Sydney:
</P>
<P>
   _ Triathlon, which has gained in popularity since it was
invented a mere 26 years ago, will provide the first medals of the
2000 Games. The women's triathlon will be held Saturday, with the
men competing a day later. The triathlon consists of a
1.5-kilometer swim in the harbor, a 40K cycle and a 10K run.
</P>
<P>
   _ Taekwondo had been a demonstration sport in 1988 and 1992,
before all demonstration sports were eliminated. Its only hope for
further Olympic recognition was to become a medal sport, and it
finally succeeded. Four men's weight classes (under 58 kg., 68 kg.,
80 kg. and over 80 kg.) and four women's weight categories (under
49kg., 57kg., 67kg., over 67kg.) will be contested.
</P>
<P>
   _ Trampoline has been added under the gymnastics umbrella, with
both men's and women's events.
</P>
<P>
   _ Women's weightlifting has been added, with seven weight
categories, while the men's classes have been reduced from 10 to
eight.
</P>
<P>
   _ Women's water polo will make its first Olympic appearance.
</P>
<P>
   _ Women's modern pentathlon will be contested for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cycling has changed some of its events on the track, with the
Olympic sprint, Madison and Keirin making their debuts in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
   _ Synchronized diving, a television-friendly crowd-pleaser, has
been added in men's and women's 3-meter and platform events.
</P>
<P>
   _ In sailing, the 49er class (mixed) has replaced the Star
class.
</P>
<P>
   _ In track and field, the women's pole vault and hammer throw
have been added, and the women's 20K walk replaces the 10K walk.
</P>
<P>
   _ In shooting, women's trap and skeet have been added.
</P>
<P>
   _ In synchronized swimming, duet has been returned to the
schedule after it was dropped in 1996. The team event remains.
</P>
<P>
   Some sports had to take a hit to accommodate all of the new
events but still limit the number of competitors staying in the
Olympic Village to about 10,000. Boxing reduced the number of
competitors, forcing some winners at the U.S. trials to clinch
their spots in subsequent regional qualifying. Wrestling cut its
number of weight categories, from 10 to eight in both freestyle and
Greco-Roman.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
