<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LEHTINEN WITH PREGNANT WIFE, NOT WITH STARS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   VAIL, Colo. _ Dallas Stars coach Ken Hitchcock said he doesn't
anticipate winger Jere Lehtinen joining the team in training camp.
Lehtinen's wife, Jaana, is pregnant with twins and her water broke
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ``His wife is due right away, the next day or so,'' Hitchcock
said. ``He's just going to stay there until everything is clear and
gone. In two or three days, he could join us, but I expect he'll
join us back in Dallas.''
</P>
<P>
   The twins came earlier than expected, but Lehtinen already had
been briefed on what to expect. His roommate on road trips,
defenseman Darryl Sydor, had twins last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``So I know what I'm getting in to,'' Lehtinen said last week.
``But it's going to be fun. I'm looking forward to it.''
</P>
<P>
   The lack of training camp isn't likely to hurt Lehtinen, who has
been skating since July 10 and who said the ankle injury that
caused him to miss all but 17 games last seasons feels good.
SYDOR'S GOOD NEWS
</P>
<P>
   The Stars received some other good news on the ankle front.
</P>
<P>
   Darryl Sydor, who tore ligaments in his left ankle during Game 6
of the Stanley Cup Finals, said he plans to get on skates while in
Vail. Don't expect anything strenuous. It's just a ``see how he
feels'' skate, but it's progress compared with a week ago when
Sydor thought he might not be ready for the team's Oct. 4 opener.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's how that thing does,'' Ken Hitchcock said.
``Struggling, struggling, struggling and then boom. He's got the
toe drag going now. The discomfort left. This thing is coming fast
now. I don't have any doubt left that he'll be ready for the start
of the season.'' NO MODANO, HULL
</P>
<P>
   Neither Mike Modano nor Brett Hull scored in Saturday in a
scrimmage. Of course, neither of them played.
</P>
<P>
   Ken Hitchcock doesn't plan to use eight of his veterans in any
of the training-camp scrimmages. Mike Keane, Richard Matvichuk,
Derian Hatcher, Sergei Zubov, Joe Nieuwendyk and Ed Belfour joined
Modano and Hull on the day off.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just don't want to burn any of them out,'' Hitchcock said.
``When you play that long, if you can buy yourself two or three
weeks, why not? It had nothing to do with injuries. It had
everything to do with three years of June.'' STUNTED GROWTH
</P>
<P>
   A lot has been made of the number of young guys in training camp
for the Stars, but young players don't necessarily equate to
competition.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'd be lying if I said a lot of positions are open,''
Hitchcock said. ``There's not. We know where we're going and it's
just a matter of where we slot people.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
